COPS in Polokwane, Limpopo have arrested three suspects for dealing and possession of drugs. The suspects were arrested after the provincial Organised Crime Investigation Unit and Crime Intelligence Counter Narcotics Unit followed up on information on Saturday, 4 March about the suspects allegedly distributing various drugs at parks near schools across the city. Colonel Malesela Ledwaba said the operatives observed the identified areas and two male suspects were spotted carrying refuse bags. ALSO READ: 'I have never taken drugs in my life! Just lean' He said they were stopped and searched and cops found 227 sachets of heroine, 21 sachets of Crystal Meth and 15 sachets of Kat all to the value of R25 000 concealed in the bags. The two suspects, aged 34 and 40, were arrested. Ledwaba said during a similar operation on Wednesday 1 March, a 44-year-old man was arrested in the Polokwane CBD after information was received about a suspect selling drugs at the taxi rank. During the arrest, the suspect was found in possession of 370 sachets of heroine, five sachets of Crystal Meth and an undisclosed amount of cash. REGISTER TO COMMENT The first suspect has already appeared in the Polokwane Magistrates Court, while the two suspects are expected to make their first court appearance on Monday, 6 March. Police investigations are still continuing. Limpopo Police Commissioner, Lieutenant-General Thembi Hadebe, praised the cops for their perseverance in ridding the communities of drugs and their dedication to apprehending those who peddle drugs. 